cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with a data structure for compressing strings with runs of letters from a large alphabet and supporting rank and select queries. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms for strings and tries, which is covered by cs.DS. The paper also discusses the lower bounds for such data structures, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). The compression aspect of the data structure involves information theory (cs.IT) and data compression (cs.DC). Finally, the paper mentions reductions to the colored predecessor problem, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
